        public XMLConfFormat getInstance()
        Description copied from interface: IPersistentFormat
        Returns an instance of this format. Clients should always call this method before calling IPersistentFormat.read(Object, CharSequence) or IPersistentFormat.write(Object) and call these methods the returned value to avoid any unintended concurrent access.

        Example IPersistentFormat<?> format = getFormat(); format.getInstance().write(new Object()) Implementing classes may return this, if read and write are implemented in a static fashion (i.e., do not use any non-static fields).
